{
  "texts": [
    "They can be simply enlarged by increasing the number of network elements to obtain higher dimensions.",
    "Single-node reservoir is composed of a single nonlinear node and a time delay loop, which can transform the input signal into a virtual high-dimensional space through time division multiplexing using single nonlinear physical nodes, such as analog circuits 57, lasers 58, etc.",
    "This type of reservoir avoids the problem of large-scale interconnection, making it more hardware friendly.",
    "However, designing and implementing appropriate delayed feedback loops is not a simple task.",
    "Continuous-medium reservoir mainly utilizes the physical phenomena of various waves in a continuous medium, such as fluid and elastic media."
  ]
}